rComments: Farrand wants you to think practical and apply what he teaches to ideal experiments. In order to succeed in his class you must understand simple concepts and how everything is related. It helps to ask questions during the lecture or attend office hours because the quizzes are graded strictly. The exams are difficult and should not be taken lightly.

This class is not meant to be easy, no matter who the teacher is.  So, you can't hold that against Farrand. I went to see him in office hours and he was very helpful and liked to anwser my questions. I liked him more after office hours. I wish I had done it earlier in the semester because I did alot better on the test when I went to his review sess
Not that bad of a lecturer, he just makes the tests really hard. Make sure you study a lot.

farrand is a really nice guy, but he doesnt seem to care very much about teaching well. sometimes he forgot to bring important info up until someone asked questions about it in lecture. he liked to trail off in office hours. record lectures. he likes to emphasize important things that will be on the exam. he also gets very excited sometimes

Wow. Third exam was a killer. The average on that class came out to be a D, so he made the final exam A LOT easier. I definitely liked Slauch's leactures much better. Seriously, watch out for the third exam (Dr. Farrand's first exam). Study his lecture notes VERY throughly and show up to class.
I hated this class. Farrand's exams were tricky and he didn't even care that a lot of them had more than one right answer. I suggest really paying attention to lectures and reading the book.

Go to lecture and take good notes.  It will save you.  Exams difficult and Farrand wasn't very fair.  The TAs put together 11 unfair MC questions from exam 3 and emailed him.  His response was pretty much too bad other than 2 questions.  Not a terrible lecturer, but Slauch was much better.
Really good professor. Makes homework relevant to what you are studying in lecture. Tests are not bad at all if you take good notes in class.

Good teacher in lecutre, horrible writer when it comes to exams. The 3rd exam was insanely difficult and the grades on this M.C. tests were very low. 4th test was very fair, but after averages near mid 50% for exam 3, it was too little too late. Be careful w/ exam 3, it took took many peoples overall grades 7-10 +%! Go to class & pay attention!

Class is difficult; study like crazy and take very detailed notes and you will do well on the tests. Going to his office hours helps a lot. Is willing to explain everything in detail outside of class. If you study for the quizzes as if they are tests, you will do well. Again, a very good professor.

I think he's more friendly than Dr. Slauch (the other professor for this class). He is intelligent, he knows a lot about the subject. Coursework is hard, and Dr. Farrand's exams are difficult. But overall, a good professor.
